# Edit Permission and Scope

- Do not run commands, edit files, or make code changes unless the user explicitly gives permission in the current conversation.
- Once the user asks for a fix, you may switch directories/branches/worktrees as needed to complete that requested fix without asking for repeated permission for each directory switch.
- When permission is granted, perform only the exact requested task and avoid related or "helpful" extra changes.
- Do not modify files outside the user-specified scope.
- If scope is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before making changes.
- Prefer small, surgical edits and report exactly what changed.
